{"sequence":61,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T01:59:00.490028363Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-9c8192c4","body":"finding_summary: The new `-fast` suffix handling is applied to OpenRouter requests as well as Codex. `build_command` feeds OpenRouter model IDs through `codex_new_session_args` / `codex_resume_args` (`src/adapters/process_backend.rs:954,979-991`), and those helpers now strip any trailing `-fast` and inject `service_tier=\"fast\"` (`src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1319-1404`). That means an OpenRouter model whose real ID ends in `-fast` will be silently rewritten to a different model and may 404 or target the wrong backend model. The added tests only exercise Codex paths (`tests/unit/process_backend_test.rs:943-1198`), so this regression is currently unguarded. severity: medium. affected_files: [src/adapters/process_backend.rs, tests/unit/process_backend_test.rs]. remediation_hint: Gate `-fast` parsing and `service_tier` injection to `BackendFamily::Codex` only, and add a regression test proving OpenRouter `...-fast` model IDs are passed through unchanged.","dedup_key":"8ef994703ce927d1fcb9c35c094c7c24eb9e27e1de6c1fecb183cb5c8b18a2c9","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415004740","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
